        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-06T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-06T03:00:00-05:00" n="1666" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/8–649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lutkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kunming</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-06T15:00:00+07:00">August 6, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 10—5:38 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. ReDeptel 56, August 3, 7 p. m. Warning contained reftel issued August 5th to
                    American citizens this consular district in covers bearing wax impression seal.
                    Americans were requested not discuss warning with aliens.</p>
                <p>Air transportation now available via CNAC, CATC, CAT and Air France, Kunming to
                    Hong Kong, Haiphong and Rangoon. Fall Canton might cut off Hong Kong. However,
                    presume flights Haiphong, Rangoon would continue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lutkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
